body:
@griesemer 

This proposal does not have a name "I propose to add symmetry to every declarations".
I don't think this should be discussed.
Functions are functions but methods are methods even if they are similar.
This intended only for OOP programmers. They will love that.
And I don't think that it is hard to read and understand such declaration style.
It use world-wide and not not complain: "Why not used such style?":

eg.
```
(class Foo) foo() string {
}

(class Foo) baz() string {
}
```

Instead of this:

```
class Foo {
   foo() string {
  }

 baz() string {
 }
}
```

The same in Go:

```go
// Want use that? Use it
func (f *foo1) baz() {
}

func (f *foo2) baz() {
}

func (f *foo1) bar() {
}

func (f *foo2) bar() {
}

// Want use that? Use it
func (f *foo1) (
  baz() {
  }

  bar() {
  }  
)

func (f *foo2) (
  baz() {
  }

  bar() {
  }  
)

```

Matter of taste. And does not forget about complex sofrware.
Implementing such software is much harder in Go language.
